SAVE THE KING steadied out of crowded quarters between horses soon after the start, saved ground off of the pace and moved up inside of foes. ACACIO stalked along the inside, bid through a vacated rail to vie at the quarter pole, but gave way at the furlong grounds and weakened. MIDNIGHT TIL DAWN was fractious loading and got outrun two wide. BOLD FORCE pressed two wide, but was outmoved by bidders on both sides at the quarter pole and faded.
